Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Thinly slice the @portobello mushrooms{2}(thinly sliced). Trim the @green beans{80} and chop into thirds. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a garlic press).

Pop your aubergine on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot add the mushrooms and stir-fry until really nicely browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Reduce the heat to medium, then add half the garlic, half the miso and a third of the soy to the pan. Continue to cook stirring constantly until the mushrooms have soaked up the flavour, ~{1-2%minutes}. Once cooked, set the pan aside off the heat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #saucepan{} on medium high heat. When hot, add the green beans and season with salt and pepper. Stir fry until charred and tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove to a #bowl{} and pop your pan back on medium high heat, add a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry, then add the onions. Stir fry the onions until soft and golden, ~{6-7%minutes}, stir in the remaining garlic and the @mild curry powder{1} and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @plain flour{8} to the mixture and cook, stirring for ~{1-2%minutes}, then pour in the @water{200}. Bring to a boil, stirring continuously and cook until the sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the green beans, aubergine, @sugar{1/2} and remaining @soy sauce{25} and @miso paste{15}, stir everything together.

Add the @udon noodles{300}, toss to coat in the sauce and cook until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

> Add a splash of water if it's reduced too much - you want it a bit saucy.

Reheat the mushrooms on medium heat. Serve the noodles with the mushrooms on top and a sprinkling of peanuts and coriander. Enjoy!